<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF82395AEBD2C34EFDBC5E04" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF82395AEBD2C34EFEAA5FA1" blockId="44.[227,341,1149,1175]" box="[227,341,1149,1175]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<heading id="5A24A609FF82395AEBD2C34EFEAA5FA1" bold="true" box="[227,341,1149,1175]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF82395AEBD2C34EFEAA5FA1" bold="true" box="[227,341,1149,1175]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF82395AEBD2C39FFDBC5E04" blockId="44.[227,1437,1196,1331]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF82395AEBD2C39FFE4C5FF0" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[227,435,1196,1222]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Genartina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="texana">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF82395AEBD2C39FFE4C5FF0" box="[227,435,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Genartina texana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather rare and found only from 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FF82395AE855C39FFC575FF0" box="[868,936,1196,1222]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Texas</collectingRegion>
in our collection (Weches Formation, till Cook Mountain Formation, but mainly from the “Stone City beds”). 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF82395AEF25C3E3FACC5FDD" author="Frizzell &amp; Dante" box="[1044,1331,1232,1259]" firstAuthor="Frizzell" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="687 - 718" refId="ref53957" refString="Frizzell D. L. &amp; Dante J. H. 1965. Otoliths of some early Cenozoic fishes of the Gulf Coast. Journal of Paleontology 39: 687 - 718." type="journal article" year="1965">Frizzell &amp; Dante (1965)</bibRefCitation>
reported its occurrence also in the Lisbon Formation of 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FF82395AE82AC3C7FC765E38" box="[795,905,1268,1294]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Alabama</collectingRegion>
. See also above, under 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF82395AEF99C3C7FAC45E38" baseAuthorityName="Priem" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1192,1339,1268,1294]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Genartina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bambergi">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF82395AEF99C3C7FAC45E38" box="[1192,1339,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">G. bambergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for the distinction of the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF82395AEBD2C269FD665EFE" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF82395AEBD2C269FD115E42" blockId="44.[227,750,1370,1397]" box="[227,750,1370,1397]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
